rComments: Ken is wonderful. He cares about the work and he cares about the students. Ken is passionate about teaching, about theatre, and about the students success. Ken is always willing to help you and give you useful feed back. I am so grateful to have had him as a prof.
SO awesome. enthusiastic and genuinely cares about the students. just as long as you...you know....do the work and...whatever... you'll be good ;)
Overly concerned with himself.  Constantly forcing students to worship him.

Ken's a gem.  He might be a little bit worn out by his heavy schedule of directing, running Factory and teaching, but he's a wise man who cares about his students and what he's doing.  Stay on his good side, work hard through the year, and you'll have a friend for life.
Ken is a really good teacher.  He knows what he is talking about and how to push his students appropriately.

Although a bit awkward when it comes to speaking and giving direction, he knows what he is doing. His understanding of human nature and intention is uncanny. He has a way of giving critism in a way that it becomes encouragement.
Ken amazing.  He's just amazing.  I can't really... it's just that sense of... You know?
Ken was a great teacher. He inspired me to become a Drama teacher. He was highly talented and taught his students with passion and insight.-MG
